			<div class="content" id="post-content-1707558">
									

<p>I've downvoted this, though with a little bit of work I would certainly upvote.</p>
<p>As it stands it feels like a disease/disorder that could exist in the real world, and while there's a point to be made for coming across as realistic, this suffers from not feeling particularly anomalous, at least to me.</p>
<p>I do like the implication of it being both man made and targeted.</p>
<p>Also it's kinda over-reliant on medical jargon.</p>

